      "date": "2017-10-24 16:10:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOverall Build Status: SUCCESS\n\nBuilder CentOS 6.7 x86_64 (BUILD) succeeded (build successful) - http://build.lustre.org/builders/CentOS%206.7%20x86_64%20%28BUILD%29/builds/11787\n\nBuilder CentOS 6.8 x86_64 (BUILD) succeeded (build successful) - http://build.lustre.org/builders/CentOS%206.8%20x86_64%20%28BUILD%29/builds/7923\n\nBuilder CentOS 7.2 x86_64 (BUILD) succeeded (build successful) - http://build.lustre.org/builders/CentOS%207.2%20x86_64%20%28BUILD%29/builds/11773\n\nBuilder Ubuntu 14.04 x86_64 (BUILD) succeeded (build successful) - http://build.lustre.org/builders/Ubuntu%2014.04%20x86_64%20%28BUILD%29/builds/11733",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "76c9754f35b90f20e4b4188af0935fcba435da27",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-24 16:18:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI think that has the potential to wake up the coordinator multiple times per seconds, which may defeat the purpose of the previous patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "8681be47bd62ad4433b315ae3573d5ca7695d977",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 529,
        "name": "Ben Evans",
        "email": "beevans@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bevans"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-24 17:21:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFrank, that's exactly what this patch is supposed to do.\n\nIf you mark 10k files for HSM to process, and the default max is 3, then the absolute fastest you can process the whole list is 55 minutes, regardless of file size, number of copy tools, bandwidth, etc.\n\nThis provides a way of signalling that all the requests have been processed, and more need to be handed out before the 1 sec interval.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d569ce1adfb9568e31eca088648560a08fa70bf8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-24 17:29:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAdding those 10000 requests will interleave with the requests being processed, and I believe we'll see the same kind of blockage as before.\n\nBTW, 3 was a really bad default before as well. That should have been changed to something more saner.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1ecd9afd405a721415d55a703053ea5fbb35a599",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-10-24 18:11:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nBuild Successful \n\nhttps://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-reviews/51679/ : SUCCESS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fe7f695780ebad30eb8ae919e6eeaccd6bb10a1f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 529,
        "name": "Ben Evans",
        "email": "beevans@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bevans"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-24 18:50:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIf that were the case, then you'd see an appreciable difference creating/submitting HAI's with the copytool enabled vs. disabled.\n\nThere is no appreciable difference in the few runs I've done.\n\nThe copytool, however keeps pace with file creation, where as before it would lag very far behind.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "8e30ef1711c887bf64921e52354c0c43ad7773e1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-24 19:03:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nok. Please fix the two booleans, and that's good for me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
