    {
      "id": "47cbe2eaade1f4cbbc1a7ac603adee9584b307ed",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-25 07:00:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> If that were the case, then you'd see an appreciable difference creating/submitting HAI's with the copytool enabled vs. disabled.\n\nActually, no. The coordinator will wake up no matter what, and it will traverse the llog. The check \"if (list_empty(&cdt->cdt_agents))\" comes after that part.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
